  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Choice Young Men'
      title: The Choice Young Men
      number: 1
      content: '  In the third year of the reign of Jehoiakim king of Judah, Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon came to Jerusalem and besieged it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord gave Jehoiakim king of Judah into his hand, along with some
        of the articles of the house of God; and he brought them into the land of
        Shinar, to the house of his god, and brought the articles into the treasury
        of his god.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the [Babylonian] king told Ashpenaz, the chief of his officials,
        to bring in some of the sons of Israel, including some from the royal family
        and from the nobles, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "young men without blemish and handsome in appearance, skillful in
        all wisdom, endowed with intelligence and discernment, and quick to understand,
        competent to stand [in the presence of the king] and able to serve in the
        king\u2019s palace. He also ordered Ashpenaz to teach them the literature
        and language of the Chaldeans. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The king assigned a daily ration for them from his finest food and
        from the wine which he drank. They were to be educated and nourished this
        way for three years so that at the end of that time they were [prepared]
        to enter the king\u2019s service. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Among them from the sons of Judah were: Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael,
        and Azariah. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Daniel\u2019s Resolve"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Resolve"
      number: 7
      content: 'The commander of the officials gave them [Babylonian] names: Daniel
        he named Belteshazzar, Hananiah he named Shadrach, Mishael he named Meshach,
        and Azariah he named Abed-nego.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Daniel made up his mind that he would not defile (taint, dishonor)
        himself with the king\u2019s finest food or with the wine which the king
        drank; so he asked the commander of the officials that he might [be excused
        so that he would] not defile himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now God granted Daniel favor and compassion in the sight of the commander
        of the officials, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and the commander of the officials said to Daniel, \u201CI am afraid
        of my lord the king, who has prearranged your food and your drink; for why
        should he see your faces looking more haggard than the young men who are
        your own age? Then you would make me forfeit my head to the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But Daniel said to the overseer whom the commander of the officials
        had appointed over Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CPlease, test your servants for ten days, and let us be given
        some vegetables to eat and water to drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then let our appearance and the appearance of the young men who eat
        the king\u2019s finest food be observed and compared by you, and deal with
        your servants in accordance with what you see.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the man listened to them in this matter and tested them for ten
        days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "At the end of ten days it seemed that they were looking better and
        healthier than all the young men who ate the king\u2019s finest food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the overseer continued to withhold their fine food and the wine
        they were to drink, and kept giving them vegetables.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'As for these four young men, God gave them knowledge and skill in
        all kinds of literature and wisdom; Daniel also understood all kinds of visions
        and dreams.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'At the end of the time set by the king to bring all the young men
        in [before him], the commander of the officials presented them to Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The king spoke with them, and among them all not one was found like
        Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah; so they were [selected and] assigned
        to stand before the king and enter his personal service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In every matter of wisdom and understanding about which the king
        consulted them, he found them ten times better than all the [learned] magicians
        and enchanters (Magi) in his whole realm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And Daniel remained there until the first year of [the reign of] King
        Cyrus [over Babylon; now this was at the end of the seventy-year exile of
        Judah (the Southern Kingdom) in Babylonia, as foretold by Jeremiah].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The King\u2019s Forgotten Dream"
      title: "The King\u2019s Forgotten Dream"
      number: 1
      content: '  In the second year (604 b.c.) of the reign of Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadnezzar
        had dreams which troubled and disturbed his spirit and [interfered with]
        his ability to sleep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the king gave a command to call the magicians, the enchanters,
        the sorcerers, and the Chaldeans to tell the king his dreams. So they came
        in and stood before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The king said to them, \u201CI had a dream, and my spirit is troubled
        and anxious to know the [content and meaning of the] dream.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Chaldeans said to the king in Aramaic, \u201CO king, live
        forever! Tell the dream to your servants, and we will declare the interpretation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The king replied to the Chaldeans, \u201CMy command is firm and unchangeable:
        if you do not reveal to me the [content of the] dream along with its interpretation,
        you shall be cut into pieces and your houses shall be made a heap of rubbish. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But if you tell [me] the [content of the] dream along with its interpretation,
        you shall receive from me gifts and rewards and great honor. So tell me the
        dream and its interpretation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They answered again, \u201CLet the king tell the dream to his servants,
        and we will explain its interpretation [to you].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The king replied, \u201CI know for certain that you are bargaining
        for time, because you have seen that my command [to you] is firm and irrevocable. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If you will not reveal to me the [content of the] dream, there is
        but one sentence for you; for you have [already] prepared lying and corrupt
        words [and you have agreed together] to speak [them] before me [hoping to
        delay your execution] until the situation is changed. Therefore, tell me
        the dream [first], and then I will know [with confidence] that you can give
        me its interpretation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The Chaldeans answered the king and said, \u201CThere is not a man
        on earth who can tell the king this matter, for no king, lord or ruler has
        ever asked such a thing as this of any magician or enchanter or Chaldean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Furthermore, what the king demands is an unusual and difficult thing
        indeed! No one except the gods can reveal it to the king, and their dwelling
        is not with [mortal] flesh.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Because of this the king was indignant and extremely furious and
        gave a command to destroy all the wise men of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the decree went out that the wise men were to be killed; and they
        looked for Daniel and his companions to put them to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Daniel replied with discretion and wisdom to Arioch, the captain
        of the king\u2019s bodyguard, who had gone out to execute the wise men of
        Babylon; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "he said to Arioch, the king\u2019s captain, \u201CWhy is the decree
        from the king so harsh and urgent?\u201D Then Arioch explained the matter
        to Daniel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Daniel went in and asked the king to appoint a date and give him
        time, so that he might reveal to the king the interpretation of the dream.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Daniel returned to his house and discussed the matter with Hananiah,
        Mishael, and Azariah, his companions, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Secret Is Revealed to Daniel'
      title: The Secret Is Revealed to Daniel
      number: 18
      content: 'in order that they might seek compassion from the God of heaven regarding
        this secret, so that Daniel and his companions would not be executed with
        the rest of the wise men of Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the secret was revealed to Daniel in a vision of the night,
        and Daniel blessed the God of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Daniel answered,\u201CBlessed be the name of God forever and ever,For
        wisdom and power belong to Him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'It is He who changes the times and the seasons;He removes kings and
        establishes kings.He gives wisdom to the wiseAnd [greater] knowledge to those
        who have understanding!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'It is He who reveals the profound and hidden things;He knows what
        is in the darkness,And the light dwells with Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I thank You and praise You, O God of my fathers,For You have given
        me wisdom and power;Even now You have made known to me what we requested
        of You,For You have made known to us [the solution to] the king\u2019s matter.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So Daniel went to Arioch, whom the king had appointed to destroy
        the wise men of Babylon; he went and said this to him: \u201CDo not execute
        the wise men of Babylon! Bring me before the king, and I will reveal to the
        king the interpretation [of his dream].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Arioch hurriedly brought Daniel before the king and said this
        to him: \u201CI have found a man among the exiles of Judah who can explain
        to the king the interpretation [of the dream].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The king said to Daniel, whose [Babylonian] name was Belteshazzar,
        \u201CAre you able to reveal to me the [content of the] dream which I have
        seen and its interpretation?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Daniel answered the king and said, \u201CRegarding the mystery about
        which the king has inquired, neither the wise men, enchanters, magicians,
        nor astrologers are able to answer the king, "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'but there is a God in heaven who reveals secrets, and He has shown
        King Nebuchadnezzar what will take place in the latter days (end of days).
        This was your dream and the vision [that appeared] in your mind while on
        your bed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'As for you, O king, as you were lying on your bed thoughts came into
        your mind about what will take place in the future; and He who reveals secrets
        has shown you what will occur. '
      comments: []
    - name: "30: The King\u2019s Dream"
      title: "The King\u2019s Dream"
      number: 30
      content: 'But as for me, this secret has not been revealed to me because my
        wisdom is greater than that of any other living man, but in order to make
        the interpretation known to the king, and so that you may understand [fully]
        the thoughts of your mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou, O king, were looking, and behold, [there was] a single
        great statue; this image, which was large and of unsurpassed splendor, stood
        before you, and its appearance was awesome and terrifying. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'As for this statue, its head was made of fine gold, its breast and
        its arms of silver, its belly and its thighs of bronze, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'its legs of iron, its feet partly of iron and partly of clay [pottery]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'As you were looking, a stone was cut out without [human] hands, and
        it struck the statue on its feet of iron and clay and crushed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: "35: The Interpretation\u2014Babylon the First Kingdom"
      title: "The Interpretation\u2014Babylon the First Kingdom"
      number: 35
      content: 'Then the iron, the clay, the bronze, the silver, and the gold were
        crushed together and became like the chaff from the summer threshing floors;
        and the wind carried them away so that not a trace of them could be found.
        And the stone that struck the statue became a great mountain and filled the
        whole earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CThis was the dream; now we will tell the king its interpretation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'You, O king, are the king of [earthly] kings, to whom the God of
        heaven has given the kingdom, the power, the strength and the glory; '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: Medo-Persia and Greece'
      title: Medo-Persia and Greece
      number: 38
      content: 'and wherever the sons of men dwell, and the beasts of the field,
        and the birds of the heavens, He has given them into your hand and has made
        you ruler over them all. You [king of Babylon] are the head of gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: Rome'
      title: Rome
      number: 39
      content: 'After you will arise another kingdom (Medo-Persia) inferior to you,
        and then a third kingdom of bronze (Greece under Alexander the Great), which
        will rule over all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Then a fourth kingdom (Rome) will be strong as iron, for iron breaks
        to pieces and shatters all things; and like iron which crushes things in
        pieces, it will break and crush all these [others]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And as you saw the feet and toes, partly of potter\u2019s clay and
        partly of iron, it will be a divided kingdom; but there will be in it some
        of the durability and strength of iron, just as you saw the iron mixed with
        common clay. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'As the [ten] toes of the feet were partly of iron and partly of clay,
        so some of the kingdom will be strong, and another part of it will be brittle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: The Divine Kingdom'
      title: The Divine Kingdom
      number: 43
      content: 'And as you saw the iron mixed with common clay, so they will combine
        with one another in the seed of men; but they will not merge [for such diverse
        things or ideologies cannot unite], even as iron does not mix with clay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'In the days of those [final ten] kings the God of heaven will set
        up a kingdom that will never be destroyed, nor will its sovereignty be left
        for another people; but it will crush and put an end to all these kingdoms,
        and it will stand forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: Daniel Promoted'
      title: Daniel Promoted
      number: 45
      content: "Just as you saw that a stone was cut out of the mountain without
        hands and that it crushed the iron, the bronze, the clay, the silver and
        the gold, the great God has revealed to the king what will take place in
        the future; so the dream is true and its interpretation is trustworthy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Then King Nebuchadnezzar fell face downward and paid respect to Daniel
        [as a great prophet of the highest God], and gave orders for an offering
        and fragrant incense to be presented to him [in honor of his God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "The king answered Daniel and said, \u201CMost certainly your God
        is the God of gods and the Lord of kings and a revealer of mysteries, since
        you have been able to reveal this mystery!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Then the king promoted Daniel [to an exalted position] and gave him
        many great gifts, and he made him ruler over the entire province of Babylon
        and chief governor over all the wise men of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: And Daniel made a request of the king, and he appointed Shadrach,
        Meshach, and Abed-nego over the affairs of the province of Babylon, while
        Daniel was at the court of the king.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The King\u2019s Golden Image"
      title: "The King\u2019s Golden Image"
      number: 1
      content: '  Nebuchadnezzar the king made a gold [-plated] image, whose height
        [including the pedestal] was sixty cubits (ninety feet) and its width six
        cubits (nine feet). He set it up on the plain of Dura in the province of
        Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Nebuchadnezzar the king sent word to assemble the satraps, the
        prefects and the governors, the counselors, the treasurers, the judges, the
        magistrates and lawyers and all the chief officials of the provinces to come
        to the dedication of the image that King Nebuchadnezzar had set up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the satraps, the prefects, the governors, the counselors, the
        treasurers, the judges, the magistrates and lawyers, and all the chief officials
        of the provinces gathered together for the dedication of the image that King
        Nebuchadnezzar had set up; and they stood before it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the herald loudly proclaimed, \u201CYou are commanded, O peoples,
        nations, and speakers of every language, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'that at the moment you hear the sound of the horn, pipe, lyre, trigon
        (four-stringed harp), dulcimer, bagpipe, and all kinds of music, you are
        to fall down and worship the golden image that King Nebuchadnezzar has set
        up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Whoever does not fall down and worship shall immediately be thrown
        into the midst of a furnace of blazing fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Worship of the Image Refused'
      title: Worship of the Image Refused
      number: 7
      content: 'So when the people heard the sound of the horn, pipe, lyre, trigon,
        dulcimer, bagpipe and all kinds of music, all the peoples, nations, and speakers
        of every language fell down and worshiped the golden image that Nebuchadnezzar
        the king had set up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'At that time certain Chaldeans came forward and brought [malicious]
        accusations against the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They said to King Nebuchadnezzar, \u201CO king, live forever! "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You, O king, have made a decree that everyone who hears the sound
        of the horn, pipe, lyre, trigon, harp, dulcimer, bagpipe, and all kinds of
        music is to fall down and worship the golden image. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Whoever does not fall down and worship shall be thrown into the midst
        of a furnace of blazing fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "There are certain Jews whom you have appointed over the administration
        of the province of Babylon, namely Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-nego. These
        men, O king, pay no attention to you; they do not serve your gods or worship
        the golden image which you have set up.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Nebuchadnezzar in a furious rage gave a command to bring Shadrach,
        Meshach, and Abed-nego; and these men were brought before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Nebuchadnezzar said to them, \u201CIs it true, Shadrach, Meshach,
        and Abed-nego, that you do not serve my gods or worship the golden image
        which I have set up? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now if you are ready, when you hear the sound of the horn, pipe,
        lyre, trigon, harp, dulcimer, and all kinds of music, to fall down and worship
        the image which I have made, very good. But if you do not worship, you shall
        be thrown at once into the midst of a furnace of blazing fire; and what god
        is there who can rescue you out of my hands?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-nego answered the king, \u201CO Nebuchadnezzar,
        we do not need to answer you on this point. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'If it be so, our God whom we serve is able to rescue us from the
        furnace of blazing fire, and He will rescue us from your hand, O king. '
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Daniel\u2019s Friends Protected"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Friends Protected"
      number: 18
      content: "But even if He does not, let it be known to you, O king, that we
        are not going to serve your gods or worship the golden image that you have
        set up!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Nebuchadnezzar was filled with fury, and his facial expression
        changed toward Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-nego. Then he gave a command that
        the furnace was to be heated seven times hotter than usual. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He commanded certain strong men in his army to tie up Shadrach, Meshach,
        and Abed-nego and to throw them into the furnace of blazing fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then these [three] men were tied up in their trousers, their coats,
        their turbans, and their other clothes, and were thrown into the midst of
        the furnace of blazing fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Because the king\u2019s command was urgent and the furnace was extremely
        hot, the flame of the fire killed the men who carried up Shadrach, Meshach,
        and Abed-nego. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But these three men, Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-nego, fell into
        the midst of the furnace of blazing fire still tied up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Nebuchadnezzar the king [looked and] was astounded, and he jumped
        up and said to his counselors, \u201CDid we not throw three men who were
        tied up into the midst of the fire?\u201D They replied to the king, \u201CCertainly,
        O king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He answered, \u201CLook! I see four men untied, walking around in
        the midst of the fire, and they are not hurt! And the appearance of the fourth
        is like a son of the gods!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Nebuchadnezzar approached the door of the blazing furnace and
        said, \u201CShadrach, Meshach, and Abed-nego, servants of the Most High God,
        come out [of there]! Come here!\u201D Then Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-nego
        came out of the midst of the fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The satraps, the prefects, the governors and the king\u2019s counselors
        gathered around them and saw that in regard to these men the fire had no
        effect on their bodies\u2014their hair was not singed, their clothes were
        not scorched or damaged, even the smell of smoke was not on them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Nebuchadnezzar responded and said, \u201CBlessed be the God of Shadrach,
        Meshach, and Abed-nego, who has sent His angel and rescued His servants who
        believed in, trusted in, and relied on Him! They violated the king\u2019s
        command and surrendered their bodies rather than serve or worship any god
        except their own God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Therefore I make a decree that any people, nation, or language that
        speaks anything offensive against the God of Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-nego
        shall be cut into pieces and their houses be made a heap of rubbish, for
        there is no other god who is able to save in this way!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Then the king caused Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-nego to prosper in
        the province of Babylon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The King Acknowledges God'
      title: The King Acknowledges God
      number: 1
      content: "  Nebuchadnezzar the king, to all the peoples, nations, and speakers
        of every language that live in all the earth: \u201CMay your peace abound! "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It has seemed good to me to declare the signs and wonders which the
        Most High God has done for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Vision of a Great Tree'
      title: The Vision of a Great Tree
      number: 3
      content: 'How great are His signsAnd how mighty are His wonders!His kingdom
        is an everlasting kingdomAnd His dominion is from generation to generation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI, Nebuchadnezzar, was at rest in my house and prospering in
        my palace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I saw a dream and it made me afraid; and the fantasies and thoughts
        and the visions [that appeared] in my mind as I lay on my bed kept alarming
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So I gave orders to bring in before me all the wise men of Babylon,
        so that they might make known to me the interpretation of the dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the magicians, the enchanters (Magi), the Chaldeans [who were
        the master astrologers] and the diviners came in, and I told them the dream,
        but they could not interpret it and make known its meaning to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But at last Daniel came in before me, whose name is Belteshazzar,
        after the name of my god, and in whom is a spirit of the holy gods; and I
        told the dream to him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u2018O Belteshazzar, chief of the magicians, because I know that
        a spirit of the holy gods is in you and no mystery baffles or troubles you,
        tell me the visions of my dream which I have seen, along with its interpretation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018The visions that passed through my mind as I lay on my bed
        were these: I was looking, and behold, there was a tree in the middle of
        the earth, and its height was great.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The tree grew large and became strongAnd its height reached to heaven,And
        it was visible to the end of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Its leaves were beautiful and its fruit abundant,And in it was food
        for all.The beasts of the field found shade under it,And the birds of the
        sky nested in its branches,And all living creatures fed themselves from it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u2018And behold, I saw in the visions of my mind as I lay on my
        bed, an angelic watcher, a holy one, descended from heaven.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He shouted aloud and said this:\u201CCut down the tree and cut off
        its branches;Shake off its leaves and scatter its fruit;Let the living creatures
        run from under itAnd the birds fly from its branches.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Nevertheless leave the stump with its roots in the ground,Bound with
        a band of iron and bronzeIn the new grass of the field;And let him be wet
        with the dew of heaven,And let him feed with the animals in the grass of
        the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Let his mind and nature be changed from a man\u2019sAnd let an animal\u2019s
        mind and nature be given to him,And let seven periods of time pass over him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "This sentence is by the decree of the angelic watchersAnd the decision
        is a command of the holy ones,So that the living may know [without any doubt]That
        the Most High [God] rules over the kingdom of mankindAnd He bestows it on
        whomever He desiresAnd sets over it the humblest and lowliest of men.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Daniel Interprets the Vision'
      title: Daniel Interprets the Vision
      number: 18
      content: "This is the dream which I, King Nebuchadnezzar, have seen. Now you,
        Belteshazzar, explain its meaning, since none of the wise men of my kingdom
        are able to reveal its interpretation to me; but you are able, for a spirit
        of the holy gods is in you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThen Daniel, whose [Babylonian] name was Belteshazzar, was
        appalled and speechless for a while [because he was deeply concerned about
        the destiny of the king], and his thoughts alarmed him. The king said, \u2018Belteshazzar,
        do not let the dream or its interpretation frighten you.\u2019 Belteshazzar
        answered, \u2018My lord, may the dream be [meant] for those who hate you
        and its message for your enemies! "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The tree that you saw, which became great and grew strong, whose
        height reached to heaven and which was visible to all the earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "whose foliage was beautiful and its fruit abundant, and on which
        was food for all, under which the beasts of the field lived, and in whose
        branches the birds of the sky nested\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'it is you, O king, who have become great and grown strong; your greatness
        has increased and it reaches to heaven, and your dominion [reaches] to the
        ends of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "In that the king saw an angelic watcher, a holy one, descending from
        heaven and saying, \u201CCut the tree down and destroy it; but leave the
        stump with its roots in the earth, but with a band of iron and bronze around
        it in the new grass of the field, and let him be wet with the dew of heaven,
        and let him feed with the beasts of the field until seven periods of time
        pass over him,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'this is the interpretation, O king: It is the decree of the Most
        High [God], which has come upon my lord the king: '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'that you shall be driven from mankind and your dwelling place shall
        be with the beasts of the field; and that you be given grass to eat like
        the cattle and be wet with the dew of heaven; and seven periods of time shall
        pass over you, until you know [without any doubt] that the Most High [God]
        rules over the kingdom of mankind and He bestows it to whomever He desires. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And in that it was commanded to leave the stump with the roots of
        the tree [in the earth], your kingdom shall be restored to you after you
        recognize (understand fully) that Heaven rules. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: The Vision Fulfilled'
      title: The Vision Fulfilled
      number: 27
      content: "Therefore, O king, let my advice to you be [considered and found]
        acceptable; break away now from your sins and exhibit your repentance by
        doing what is right, and from your wickedness by showing mercy to the poor,
        so that [if you repent] there may possibly be a continuance of your prosperity
        and tranquility and a healing of your error.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CAll this happened to Nebuchadnezzar the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Twelve months later he was walking on the upper level of the royal
        palace of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The king said thoughtfully, \u2018Is not this the great Babylon which
        I myself have built as the royal residence and seat of government by the
        might of my power and for the honor and glory of my majesty?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "While the words were still in the king\u2019s mouth, a voice came
        [as if falling] from heaven, saying, \u2018O King Nebuchadnezzar, to you
        it is declared: \u201CThe kingdom has been removed from you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "and you will be driven away from mankind, and your dwelling place
        will be with the animals of the field. You will be given grass to eat like
        the cattle, and seven periods of time will pass over you until you know [without
        any doubt] that the Most High God rules over the kingdom of mankind and He
        bestows it on whomever He desires.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Immediately the word concerning Nebuchadnezzar was fulfilled. He
        was driven away from mankind and began eating grass like cattle, and his
        body was wet with the dew of heaven until his hair had grown like eagles\u2019
        feathers and his nails were like birds\u2019 claws.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CBut at the end of the days [that is, at the seven periods of
        time], I, Nebuchadnezzar, raised my eyes toward heaven, and my understanding
        and reason returned to me; and I blessed the Most High [God] and I praised
        and honored and glorified Him who lives forever,For His dominion is an everlasting
        dominion;And His kingdom endures from generation to generation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "All the inhabitants of the earth are regarded as nothing.But He does
        according to His will in the host of heavenAnd among the inhabitants of the
        earth;And no one can hold back His handOr say to Him, \u2018What have You
        done?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Now at the same time my reason returned to me; and for the glory
        of my kingdom, my majesty and splendor were returned to me, and my counselors
        and my nobles began seeking me out; so I was re-established in my kingdom,
        and still more greatness [than before] was added to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Now I, Nebuchadnezzar, praise and exalt and honor the King of heaven,
        for all His works are true and faithful and His ways are just, and He is
        able to humiliate and humble those who walk in [self-centered, self-righteous]
        pride.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Belshazzar\u2019s Feast"
      title: "Belshazzar\u2019s Feast"
      number: 1
      content: '  Belshazzar the king [who was a descendant of Nebuchadnezzar] gave
        a great feast for a thousand of his nobles, and he was drinking his wine
        in the presence of the thousand [guests]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Belshazzar, as he tasted the wine, gave a command to bring in the
        gold and silver vessels which his father Nebuchadnezzar had taken out of
        the temple which was in Jerusalem, so that the king and his nobles, his wives
        and his concubines might drink from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then they brought in the gold and silver vessels that had been taken
        out of the temple, the house of God which was in Jerusalem; and the king
        and his nobles, his wives and his concubines drank from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They drank the wine and praised the gods of gold and silver, of bronze,
        iron, wood and stone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Suddenly the fingers of a man\u2019s hand appeared and began writing
        opposite the lampstand on [a well-lit area of] the plaster of the wall of
        the king\u2019s palace, and the king saw the part of the hand that did the
        writing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the king\u2019s face grew pale, and his thoughts alarmed him;
        the joints and muscles of his hips and back weakened and his knees began
        knocking together. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The king called aloud to bring in the enchanters (Magi), the Chaldeans
        [who were master astrologers] and the diviners. The king said to the wise
        men of Babylon, \u201CWhoever can read this writing and explain its interpretation
        to me shall be clothed with purple and have a chain of gold put around his
        neck, and have authority as the third ruler in the kingdom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then all the king\u2019s wise men came in, but they could not read
        the writing or reveal to the king its interpretation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then King Belshazzar was greatly perplexed, his face became even
        paler, and his nobles were bewildered and alarmed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now the queen [mother], overhearing the [excited] words of the king
        and his nobles, came into the banquet area. The queen [mother] spoke and
        said, \u201CO king, live forever! Do not be alarmed at your thoughts or let
        your face be changed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "There is a man in your kingdom in whom is a spirit of the holy gods;
        and in the days of your father, illumination, understanding and wisdom like
        the wisdom of the gods were found in him. And King Nebuchadnezzar, your father\u2014your
        father the king, appointed him chief of the magicians, enchanters, Chaldeans
        and diviners. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Daniel Interprets Handwriting on the Wall'
      title: Daniel Interprets Handwriting on the Wall
      number: 12
      content: "It was because an extraordinary spirit, knowledge and insight, the
        ability to interpret dreams, clarify riddles, and solve complex problems
        were found in this Daniel, whom the king named Belteshazzar. Now let Daniel
        be called and he will give the interpretation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Daniel was brought in before the king. And the king said to
        Daniel, \u201CAre you that Daniel who is one of the sons of the exiles of
        Judah, whom my father the king brought from Judah? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have heard of you, that a spirit of the gods is in you, and that
        illumination, insight, and extraordinary wisdom have been found in you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the wise men and the enchanters, were brought in before me so
        that they might read this writing and reveal its meaning to me, but they
        could not give the interpretation of the message. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But I personally have heard about you, that you are able to make
        interpretations and solve complex problems. Now if you are able to read the
        writing and reveal its interpretation to me, you shall be clothed with purple
        and have a chain of gold put around your neck, and you shall have authority
        as the third ruler in the kingdom.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Daniel answered and said before the king, \u201CKeep your gifts
        for yourself and give your rewards to someone else; however, I will read
        the writing to the king and reveal the interpretation to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'O king, the Most High God gave Nebuchadnezzar your father a kingdom
        and greatness and glory and majesty; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and because of the greatness that He gave him, all the peoples, nations,
        and speakers of every language trembled and feared him. Whomever he wished
        he killed, and whomever he wished he kept alive; whomever he wished he promoted
        and whomever he wished he humbled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But when his heart was lifted up and his spirit became so proud that
        he behaved arrogantly, he was deposed from his royal throne and his glory
        was taken away from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He was also driven from mankind, and his mind was made like that
        of an animal, and his dwelling place was with the wild donkeys. He was given
        grass to eat like cattle, and his body was wet with the dew of heaven until
        he came to know [without any doubt] that the Most High God rules over the
        kingdom of mankind and He appoints it to whomever He wills. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And you, his son, O Belshazzar, have not humbled your heart (mind),
        even though you knew all this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And you have exalted yourself against the Lord of heaven, and the
        vessels of His house have been brought before you, and you and your nobles,
        your wives and your concubines have been drinking wine from them; and you
        have praised the gods of silver and gold, of bronze, iron, wood and stone,
        which do not see or hear or understand. But the God who holds in His hand
        your breath of life and your ways you have not honored and glorified [but
        have dishonored and defied]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then the hand was sent from the presence [of the Most High God],
        and this inscription was written:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CThis is the inscription that was written, \u2018mene, mene,
        tekel, upharsin [numbered, numbered, weighed, and divided].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "This is the interpretation of the message: \u2018mene\u2019\u2014God
        has numbered the days of your kingdom and put an end to it; "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u2018tekel\u2019\u2014you have been weighed on the scales [of righteousness]
        and found deficient; "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u2018peres\u2019\u2014your kingdom has been divided and given over
        to the Medes and Persians.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Belshazzar gave the command, and Daniel was clothed with purple
        and a chain of gold was put around his neck, and a proclamation concerning
        him was issued [declaring] that he now had authority as the third ruler in
        the kingdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'During that same night Belshazzar the [last] Chaldean king was slain
        [by troops of the invading army]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: So Darius the Mede received the kingdom; he was about the age of sixty-two.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Daniel Serves Darius'
      title: Daniel Serves Darius
      number: 1
      content: '  It seemed good to Darius [who became king after Belshazzar] to
        appoint over the kingdom 120 satraps who would be in charge throughout the
        kingdom, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and over them three chief commissioners (of whom Daniel was one),
        that these satraps might be accountable to them, so that the king would have
        no loss [from disloyalty or mismanagement]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then this Daniel, because of the extraordinary spirit within him,
        began distinguishing himself among the commissioners and the satraps, and
        the king planned to appoint him over the entire realm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the [other two] commissioners and the satraps began trying to
        find a reason to bring a complaint against Daniel concerning the [administration
        of the] kingdom; but they could find no reason for an accusation or evidence
        of corruption, because he was faithful [a man of high moral character and
        personal integrity], and no negligence or corruption [of any kind] was found
        in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then these men said, \u201CWe will not find any basis for an accusation
        against this Daniel unless we find something against him in connection with
        the law of his God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then these commissioners and satraps agreed to approach the king
        and said to him, \u201CKing Darius, live forever! "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All the commissioners of the kingdom, the prefects and the satraps,
        the counselors and the governors have consulted and agreed together that
        the king should establish a royal statute and enforce an injunction that
        anyone who petitions (prays to) any god or man besides you, O king, during
        the next thirty days, shall be thrown into the den of lions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now, O king, establish the injunction and sign the document so that
        it may not be changed, in accordance with the law of the Medes and Persians,
        which [insures that it] may not be altered or revoked.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So King Darius signed the document, that is, the injunction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now when Daniel knew that the document was signed, he went into his
        house (now in his roof chamber his windows were open toward Jerusalem); he
        continued to get down on his knees three times a day, praying and giving
        thanks before his God, as he had been doing previously. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then, by agreement, these men came [together] and found Daniel praying
        and making requests before his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then they approached and spoke before the king regarding his injunction,
        \u201CHave you not signed an injunction that anyone who petitions (prays
        to) any god or man except you, O king, within the designated thirty days,
        is to be thrown into the den of lions?\u201D The king answered, \u201CThe
        statement is true, in accordance with the law of the Medes and Persians,
        which may not be altered or revoked.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then they answered and said before the king, \u201CDaniel, who is
        one of the exiles from Judah, does not pay any attention to you, O king,
        or to the injunction which you have signed, but keeps praying [to his God]
        three times a day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then, as soon as the king heard these words, he was deeply distressed
        [over what he had done] and set his mind on rescuing Daniel; and he struggled
        until the sun went down [trying to work out a way] to save him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Daniel in the Den of Lions'
      title: Daniel in the Den of Lions
      number: 15
      content: "Then, by agreement, these same men came to the king and said, \u201CKnow,
        O king, that it is a law of the Medes and Persians that no injunction or
        statute which the king establishes may be altered or revoked.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the king gave a command, and Daniel was brought and thrown into
        the den of lions. The king said to Daniel, \u201CMay your God, whom you constantly
        serve, rescue you Himself!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'A stone was brought and laid over the mouth of the den; and the king
        sealed it with his own signet ring and with the signet rings of his nobles,
        so that nothing would be changed concerning Daniel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the king returned to his palace and spent the night fasting;
        and no music or entertainment was brought before him, and he remained unable
        to sleep.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the king arose at dawn, at the break of day, and hurried to
        the den of lions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When he had come near the den, he called out to Daniel with a troubled
        voice. The king said to Daniel, \u201CO Daniel, servant of the living God,
        has your God, whom you constantly serve, been able to rescue you from the
        lions?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Daniel spoke to the king, \u201CO king, live forever! "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "My God has sent His angel and has shut the mouths of the lions so
        that they have not hurt me, because I was found innocent before Him; and
        also before you, O king, I have committed no crime.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then the king was greatly pleased and ordered that Daniel be taken
        out of the den. So Daniel was taken out of the den, and no injury whatever
        was found on him, because he believed in and relied on and trusted in his
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The king then gave a command, and those men who had maliciously accused
        Daniel were brought and thrown into the den of lions, they, their children
        and their wives; and before they reached the bottom of the den, the lions
        overpowered them and crushed all their bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Darius the king wrote to all the peoples, nations, and speakers
        of every language who were living in all the land: \u201CMay peace abound
        to you! "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I issue a decree that in all the dominion of my kingdom men are to
        [reverently] fear and tremble before the God of Daniel,For He is the living
        God, enduring and steadfast forever,And His kingdom is one which will not
        be destroyed,And His dominion will be forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He rescues and saves and performs signs and wondersIn heaven and
        on earth\u2014He who has rescued Daniel from the power of the lions.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: So this [man] Daniel prospered and enjoyed success in the reign of
        Darius and in the reign of Cyrus the Persian.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Vision of the Four Beasts'
      title: Vision of the Four Beasts
      number: 1
      content: '  In the first year of Belshazzar king of Babylon Daniel had a dream
        and visions appeared in his mind as he lay on his bed; then he wrote the
        dream down and related a summary of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Daniel said, \u201CI saw in my vision by night, and behold, the four
        winds of heaven were stirring up the great sea (the nations). "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And four great beasts, each different from the other, were coming
        up out of the sea [in succession]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The first (the Babylonian Empire under Nebuchadnezzar) was like a
        lion and had the wings of an eagle. I kept looking until its wings were plucked,
        and it was lifted up from the ground and made to stand on two feet like a
        man; a human mind was given to it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And behold, another beast, a second one (the Medo-Persian Empire),
        was like a bear, and it was raised up on one side (domain), and three ribs
        were in its mouth between its teeth; and it was told, \u2018Arise, devour
        much meat.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "After this I kept looking, and behold, another one (the Greek Empire
        of Alexander the Great), like a leopard, which had on its back four wings
        like those of a bird; the beast also had four heads (Alexander\u2019s generals,
        his successors), and power to rule was given to it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'After this I kept looking in the night visions, and behold, [I saw]
        a fourth beast (the Roman Empire), terrible and extremely strong; and it
        had huge iron teeth. It devoured and crushed and trampled down what was left
        with its feet. It was different from all the beasts that came before it,
        and it had ten horns (ten kings). '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Ancient of Days Reigns'
      title: The Ancient of Days Reigns
      number: 8
      content: 'While I was considering the horns, behold, there came up among them
        another horn, a little one, and three of the first horns were pulled up by
        the roots before it; and behold, in this horn were eyes like the eyes of
        a man and a mouth boasting of great things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CI kept lookingUntil thrones were set up,And the Ancient of
        Days (God) took His seat;His garment was white as snowAnd the hair of His
        head like pure wool.His throne was flames of fire;Its wheels were a burning
        fire.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'A river of fire was flowingAnd coming out from before Him;A thousand
        thousands were attending Him,And ten thousand times ten thousand were standing
        before Him;The court was seated,And the books were opened.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then I kept looking because of the sound of the great and boastful
        words which the horn was speaking. I kept looking until the beast was slain,
        and its body destroyed and given to be burned with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Son of Man Presented'
      title: The Son of Man Presented
      number: 12
      content: 'As for the rest of the beasts, their power was taken away; yet their
        lives were prolonged [for the length of their lives was fixed] for a predetermined
        time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CI kept looking in the night visions,And behold, on the clouds
        of heavenOne like a Son of Man was coming,And He came up to the Ancient of
        DaysAnd was presented before Him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Vision Interpreted'
      title: The Vision Interpreted
      number: 14
      content: 'And to Him (the Messiah) was given dominion (supreme authority),Glory
        and a kingdom,That all the peoples, nations, and speakers of every languageShould
        serve and worship Him.His dominion is an everlasting dominionWhich will not
        pass away;And His kingdom is oneWhich will not be destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAs for me, Daniel, my spirit was distressed and anxious within
        me, and the visions [that appeared] in my mind kept alarming (agitating)
        me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I approached one of those who stood by and began asking him the exact
        meaning of all this. So he told me and explained to me the interpretation
        of the things: '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018These four great beasts are four kings who will arise from
        the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But the saints (believers) of the Most High [God] will receive the
        kingdom and possess the kingdom forever, for all ages to come.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThen I wished to know the exact meaning of the fourth beast,
        which was different from all the others, extremely dreadful, with teeth of
        iron and claws of bronze, which devoured, crushed and trampled down what
        was left with its feet, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and the meaning of the ten horns (kings) that were on its head and
        the other horn which came up later, and before which three of the horns fell,
        specifically, that horn which had eyes and a mouth that boasted great things
        and which looked larger than the others. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'As I kept looking, that horn was making war with the saints (believers)
        and overpowering them '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'until the Ancient of Days came and judgment was passed in favor of
        the saints of the Most High [God], and the time arrived when the saints (believers)
        took possession of the kingdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CThus the angel said, \u2018The fourth beast shall be a fourth
        kingdom on earth, which will be different from all other kingdoms and will
        devour the whole earth and tread it down, and crush it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'As for the ten horns, out of this kingdom ten kings will arise; and
        another will arise after them, and he will be different from the former ones,
        and he will subdue three kings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He will speak words against the Most High [God] and wear down the
        saints of the Most High, and he will intend to change the times and the law;
        and they will be given into his hand for a time, [two] times, and half a
        time [three and one-half years]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But the court [of the Most High] will sit in judgment, and his dominion
        will be taken away, [first to be] consumed [gradually] and [then] to be destroyed
        forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the kingdom and the dominion and the greatness of all the kingdoms
        under the whole heaven will be given to the people of the saints (believers)
        of the Most High; His kingdom will be an everlasting kingdom, and all the
        dominions will serve and obey Him.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CThis is the end of the matter. As for me, Daniel, my [waking]
        thoughts were extremely troubling and alarming and my face grew pale; but
        I kept the matter [of the vision and the angel\u2019s explanation] to myself.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Vision of the Ram and Goat'
      title: Vision of the Ram and Goat
      number: 1
      content: '  In the third year of the reign of King Belshazzar a [second] vision
        appeared to me, Daniel, [this was two years] after the one that first appeared
        to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I looked in the vision and it seemed that I was at the citadel of
        Susa, [the capital of Persia], which is in the province of Elam; and I looked
        in the vision and I saw myself by the Ulai Canal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then I raised my eyes and looked, and behold, there in front of the
        canal stood a [lone] ram (the Medo-Persian Empire) which had two horns. The
        two horns were high, but one (Persia) was higher than the other (Media),
        and the higher one came up last. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I saw the ram (Medo-Persia) charging westward and northward and southward;
        no beast could stand before him, nor was there anyone who could rescue [anything]
        from his power, but he did as he pleased and magnified himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'As I was observing [this], behold, a male goat (Greece) was coming
        from the west [rushing] across the face of the whole earth without touching
        the ground; and the goat had a conspicuous and remarkable horn (Alexander
        the Great) between his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He came up to the ram that had the two horns, which I had seen standing
        in front of the canal, and charged at him in [the fury of] his power and
        wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '[In my vision] I saw him come close to the ram (Medo-Persia), and
        he was filled with rage toward him; and the goat (Greece) struck the ram
        and shattered his two horns, and the ram had no strength to stand before
        him. So the goat threw him to the ground and trampled on him, and there was
        no one who could rescue the ram from his power. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Little Horn'
      title: The Little Horn
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the male goat magnified himself exceedingly, and when he was
        [young and] strong, the great horn (Alexander) was [suddenly] broken; and
        in its place there came up four prominent horns [among whom the kingdom was
        divided, one] toward [each of] the four winds of heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Out of one of them (Antiochus IV Epiphanes) came forth a rather small
        horn [but one of irreverent presumption and profane pride] which grew exceedingly
        powerful toward the south, toward the east, and toward the Beautiful Land
        (Israel). '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And [in my vision] this horn grew up to the host of heaven, and caused
        some of the host and some of the stars to fall to the earth, and it trampled
        on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Indeed, it magnified itself to be equal with the Commander of the
        host [of heaven]; and it took away from Him the daily sacrifice (burnt offering),
        and the place of His sanctuary was thrown down (profaned). '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Because of the transgression [of God\u2019s people\u2014their irreverence
        and ungodliness] the host will be given over to the wicked horn, along with
        the regular sacrifice; and righteousness and truth will be flung to the ground,
        and the horn will do as it pleases [by divine permission] and prosper. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then I heard a holy one (angel) speaking, and another holy one said
        to the one who was speaking, \u201CHow much time will be required to complete
        the vision regarding the regular sacrifice, the transgression that brings
        horror, and the trampling underfoot of both the sanctuary and the host [of
        the people]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Interpretation of the Vision'
      title: Interpretation of the Vision
      number: 14
      content: "He said to me, \u201CFor 2,300 evenings and mornings; then the sanctuary
        will be cleansed and properly restored.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When I, Daniel, had seen the vision, I sought to understand it; then
        behold, standing before me was one who looked like a man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I heard the voice of a man between the banks of the Ulai, which
        called out and said, \u201CGabriel, give this man (Daniel) an understanding
        of the vision.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So he came near where I was standing, and when he came I was frightened
        and fell face downward; but he said to me, \u201CUnderstand, son of man,
        that the [fulfillment of the] vision pertains to [events that will occur
        in] the time of the end.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now as he (Gabriel) was speaking with me, I drifted into a deep sleep
        (unconsciousness) with my face to the ground; but he touched me and made
        me stand [where I had stood before]. '
      comments: []
    - name: "19: The Ram\u2019s Identity"
      title: "The Ram\u2019s Identity"
      number: 19
      content: "He said, \u201CBehold, I am going to let you know what will happen
        during the final time of the indignation and wrath [of God upon the ungodly],
        for it concerns the appointed time of the end.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Goat'
      title: The Goat
      number: 20
      content: 'The ram which you saw with the two horns represents the kings of
        Media and Persia.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The shaggy (rough-coated) male goat represents the kingdom of Greece,
        and the great horn between his eyes is the first king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Regarding the shattered horn and the four others that arose in its
        place, four kingdoms will rise from his (Alexander\u2019s) nation, although
        not with his power and heritage.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'At the latter period of their reign,When the transgressors have finished,A
        king will ariseInsolent and skilled in intrigue and cunning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'His power will be mighty, but not by his own power;And he will corrupt
        and destroy in an astonishing mannerAnd [he will] prosper and do exactly
        as he wills;He shall corrupt and destroy mighty men and the holy people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And through his shrewdnessHe will cause deceit to succeed by his
        hand (influence);He will magnify himself in his mind,He will corrupt and
        destroy many who enjoy a false sense of security.He will also stand up and
        oppose the Prince of princes,But he will be broken, and that by no human
        hand [but by the hand of God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The vision of the evenings and the morningsWhich has been told [to
        you] is true.But keep the vision a secret,For it has to do with many days
        in the now distant future.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And I, Daniel, was exhausted and was sick for [several] days. Afterward
        I got up and continued with the king\u2019s business; but I was astounded
        at the vision, and there was no one who could explain it."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Daniel\u2019s Prayer for His People"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Prayer for His People"
      number: 1
      content: "  In the first year of Darius the son of Ahasuerus, of Median descent,
        who was made king over the realm of the Chaldeans\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'in the first year of his reign, I, Daniel, understood from the books
        the number of years which, according to the word of the Lord to Jeremiah
        the prophet, must pass before the desolations [which had been] pronounced
        on Jerusalem would end; and it was seventy years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So I directed my attention to the Lord God to seek Him by prayer
        and supplications, with fasting, sackcloth and ashes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I prayed to the Lord my God and confessed and said, \u201CO Lord,
        the great and awesome God, who keeps His covenant and extends lovingkindness
        toward those who love Him and keep His commandments, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'we have sinned and committed wrong, and have behaved wickedly and
        have rebelled, turning away from Your commandments and ordinances. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Further, we have not listened to and heeded Your servants the prophets,
        who spoke in Your name to our kings, our princes and our fathers, and to
        all the people of the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CRighteousness belongs to You, O Lord, but to us confusion and
        open shame, as it is this day\u2014to the men of Judah, to the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem, and to all Israel, those who are nearby and those who are far
        away, in all the countries to which You have driven them, because of the
        [treacherous] acts of unfaithfulness which they have committed against You. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "O Lord, to us belong confusion and open shame\u2014to our kings,
        to our princes, and to our fathers\u2014because we have sinned against You. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'To the Lord our God belong mercy and lovingkindness and forgiveness,
        for we have rebelled against Him; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and we have not obeyed the voice of the Lord our God by walking in
        His laws which He set before us through His servants the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yes, all Israel has transgressed Your law, even turning aside, not
        obeying Your voice; so the curse has been poured out on us and the oath which
        is written in the Law of Moses the servant of God, because we have sinned
        against Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And He has carried out completely His [threatening] words which He
        had spoken against us and against our rulers [the kings, princes, and judges]
        who ruled us, to bring on us a great tragedy; for under the whole heaven
        there has not been done anything [so dreadful] like that which [He commanded
        and] was done to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Just as it is written in the Law of Moses, all this tragedy has come
        on us. Yet we have not wholeheartedly begged for forgiveness and sought the
        favor of the Lord our God by turning from our wickedness and paying attention
        to and placing value in Your truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore the Lord has kept the tragedy ready and has brought it
        on us, for the Lord our God is [uncompromisingly] righteous and openly just
        in all His works which He does\u2014He keeps His word; and we have not obeyed
        His voice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAnd now, O Lord our God, who brought Your people out of the
        land of Egypt with a mighty hand and who made for Yourself a name, as it
        is today\u2014we have sinned, we have been wicked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'O Lord, in accordance with all Your righteous and just acts, please
        let Your anger and Your wrath turn away from Your city Jerusalem, Your holy
        mountain. Because of our sins and the wickedness of our fathers, Jerusalem
        and Your people have become an object of scorn and a contemptuous byword
        to all who are around us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now therefore, our God, listen to (heed) the prayer of Your servant
        (Daniel) and his supplications, and for Your own sake let Your face shine
        on Your desolate sanctuary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'O my God, incline Your ear and hear; open Your eyes and look at our
        desolations and the city which is called by Your name; for we are not presenting
        our supplications before You because of our own merits and righteousness,
        but because of Your great mercy and compassion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Gabriel Brings an Answer'
      title: Gabriel Brings an Answer
      number: 19
      content: "O Lord, hear! O Lord, forgive! O Lord, listen and take action! Do
        not delay, for Your own sake, O my God, because Your city and Your people
        are called by Your name.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'While I was still speaking and praying, and confessing my sin and
        the sin of my people Israel, and presenting my supplication before the Lord
        my God in behalf of the holy mountain of my God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'while I was still speaking in prayer and extremely exhausted, the
        man Gabriel, whom I had seen in the earlier vision, came to me about the
        time of the evening sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He instructed me and he talked with me and said, \u201CO Daniel,
        I have now come to give you insight and wisdom and understanding. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Seventy Weeks and the Messiah'
      title: Seventy Weeks and the Messiah
      number: 23
      content: 'At the beginning of your supplications, the command [to give you
        an answer] was issued, and I have come to tell you, for you are highly regarded
        and greatly beloved. Therefore consider the message and begin to understand
        the [meaning of the] vision.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CSeventy weeks [of years, or 490 years] have been decreed for
        your people and for your holy city (Jerusalem), to finish the transgression,
        to make an end of sins, to make atonement (reconciliation) for wickedness,
        to bring in everlasting righteousness (right-standing with God), to seal
        up vision and prophecy and prophet, and to anoint the Most Holy Place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So you are to know and understand that from the issuance of the command
        to restore and rebuild Jerusalem until [the coming of] the Messiah (the Anointed
        One), the Prince, there will be seven weeks [of years] and sixty-two weeks
        [of years]; it will be built again, with [a city] plaza and moat, even in
        times of trouble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then after the sixty-two weeks [of years] the Anointed One will be
        cut off [and denied His Messianic kingdom] and have nothing [and no one to
        defend Him], and the people of the [other] prince who is to come will destroy
        the city and the sanctuary. Its end will come with a flood; even to the end
        there will be war; desolations are determined. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he will enter into a binding and irrevocable covenant with the
        many for one week (seven years), but in the middle of the week he will stop
        the sacrifice and grain offering [for the remaining three and one-half years];
        and on the wing of abominations will come one who makes desolate, even until
        the complete destruction, one that is decreed, is poured out on the one who
        causes the horror.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Daniel Is Terrified by a Vision'
      title: Daniel Is Terrified by a Vision
      number: 1
      content: '  In the third year of Cyrus king of Persia a message was revealed
        to Daniel, who was named Belteshazzar; and the message was true and it referred
        to great conflict (warfare, misery). And he understood the message and had
        an understanding of the vision.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In those days I, Daniel, had been mourning for three entire weeks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I ate no tasty food, nor did any meat or wine enter my mouth; and
        I did not anoint (refresh, groom) myself at all for the full three weeks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On the twenty-fourth day of the first month, as I was on the bank
        of the great river Hiddekel [which is the Tigris], '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I raised my eyes and looked, and behold, there was a certain man
        dressed in linen, whose loins were girded with [a belt of] pure gold of Uphaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'His body also was like beryl [with a golden luster], his face had
        the appearance of lightning, his eyes were like flaming torches, his arms
        and his feet like the gleam of burnished bronze, and the sound of his words
        was like the noise of a multitude [of people or the roaring of the sea]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I, Daniel, alone saw the vision [of this heavenly being], for
        the men who were with me did not see the vision; nevertheless, a great panic
        overwhelmed them, so they ran away to hide themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So I was left alone and saw this great vision; yet no strength was
        left in me, for my normal appearance turned to a deathly pale, and I grew
        weak and faint [with fright]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Daniel Comforted'
      title: Daniel Comforted
      number: 9
      content: 'Then I heard the sound of his words; and when I heard the sound of
        his words, I fell on my face in a deep sleep, with my face toward the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then behold, a hand touched me and set me unsteadily on my hands
        and knees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So he said to me, \u201CO Daniel, you highly regarded and greatly
        beloved man, understand the words that I am about to say to you and stand
        upright, for I have now been sent to you.\u201D And while he was saying this
        word to me, I stood up trembling. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CDo not be afraid, Daniel, for from the
        first day that you set your heart on understanding this and on humbling yourself
        before your God, your words were heard, and I have come in response to your
        words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the prince of the kingdom of Persia was standing in opposition
        to me for twenty-one days. Then, behold, Michael, one of the chief [of the
        celestial] princes, came to help me, for I had been left there with the kings
        of Persia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now I have come to make you understand what will happen to your people
        in the latter days, for the vision is in regard to the days yet to come.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When he had spoken to me according to these words, I turned my face
        toward the ground and was speechless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And behold, one who resembled the sons of men touched my lips. Then
        I opened my mouth and spoke and said to him who was standing before me, \u201CO
        my lord, because of the vision anguish has come upon me, and I have retained
        no strength. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For how can such a [weakened] servant of my lord talk with such [a
        being] as my lord? For now there remains no strength in me, nor has any breath
        been left in me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the one (Gabriel) whose appearance was like that of a man touched
        me again, and he strengthened me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He said, \u201CO man, highly regarded and greatly beloved, do not
        be afraid. Peace be to you; take courage and be strong.\u201D Now when he
        had spoken to me, I was strengthened and said, \u201CLet my lord speak, for
        you have strengthened me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then he said, \u201CDo you understand [fully] why I came to you?
        Now I shall return to fight against the [hostile] prince of Persia; and when
        I have gone, behold, the prince of Greece is about to come. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But I (Gabriel) will tell you what is inscribed in the writing of
        truth. There is no one who stands firmly with me and strengthens himself
        against these [hostile spirit forces] except Michael, your prince [the guardian
        of your nation].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Conflicts to Come'
      title: Conflicts to Come
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAlso I, in the first year of Darius the Mede, I (Gabriel)
        arose to be an encouragement and a protection for him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And now I will tell you the truth. Behold, three more kings are going
        to arise in Persia. Then a fourth will become far richer than all of them.
        When he becomes strong through his riches he will stir up the whole empire
        against the realm of Greece. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then a mighty [warlike, threatening] king will arise who will rule
        with great authority and do as he pleases. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But as soon as he (Alexander) has risen, his kingdom will be broken
        [by his death] and divided toward the four winds of heaven [the north, south,
        east, and west], but not to his descendants, nor according to the [Grecian]
        authority with which he ruled, for his kingdom will be torn out and uprooted
        and given to others (his four generals) to the exclusion of these.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThen the king of the South (Egypt) will be strong, along with
        one of his princes who will be stronger than he and have dominance over him;
        his domain will be a great dominion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'After some years the Syrian king of the North and the Egyptian king
        of the South will make an alliance; the daughter (Berenice) of the king of
        the South will come to the king of the North to make an equitable and peaceful
        agreement (marriage); but she will not retain the power of her position,
        nor will he retain his power. She will be handed over with her attendants
        and her father as well as he who supported her in those times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But out of a branch of her [familial] roots will one (her brother,
        Ptolemy III Euergetes I) arise in his place, and he will come against the
        [Syrian] army and enter the fortress of the king of the North, and he will
        deal with them and will prevail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Also he will carry off to Egypt their [Syrian] gods with their cast
        images and their precious and costly treasure of silver and of gold, and
        he will refrain from waging war against the king of the North for some years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the king of the North will come into the realm of the king of
        the South, but he will retreat to his own country [badly defeated].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CHis sons will prepare for battle and assemble a multitude of
        great forces; which will keep on coming and overflow [the land], and pass
        through, so that they may again wage war as far as his fortress. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The king of the South (Ptolemy IV Philopator of Egypt) will be enraged
        and go out and fight with the king of the North (Antiochus III the Great);
        and the Syrian king will raise a great multitude (army), but the multitude
        shall be given into the hand of the Egyptian king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When the multitude (army) is captured and carried away, the heart
        of the Egyptian king will be proud (arrogant), and he will cause tens of
        thousands to fall, but he will not prevail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the king of the North will again raise a multitude (army) greater
        than the one before, and after several years he will advance with a great
        army and substantial equipment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIn those times many will rise up against the king of the South
        (Egypt); also the violent men among your own people will arise in order to
        fulfill the [earlier] visions, but they will fail. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the king of the North (Syria) will come and build up siege ramps
        and capture a well-fortified city. The forces of the South will not stand
        their ground, not even the finest troops, for there will be no strength to
        stand [against the Syrian king]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But he (Syria) who comes against him (Egypt) will do exactly as he
        pleases, and no one will be able to stand against him; he (Antiochus III
        the Great) will also stay for a time in the Beautiful and Glorious Land [of
        Israel], with destruction in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He will be determined to come with the power of his entire kingdom,
        and propose equitable conditions and terms of peace, which he will put into
        effect [by making an agreement with the king of the South]. He will also
        give him his daughter (Cleopatra I), in an attempt to overthrow the kingdom,
        but it will not succeed or be to his advantage. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "After this, he (Antiochus III the Great, King of Syria) will turn
        his attention to the islands and coastlands and capture many [of them]. But
        a commander (Lucius Scipio Asiaticus of Rome) will put an end to his aggression
        [toward Rome\u2019s territorial interests]; in fact, he will repay his insolence
        and turn his audacity back upon him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then he will turn back toward the fortresses of his own land [of
        Syria], but he will stumble and fall and not be found.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThen in his place one (his eldest son, Seleucus IV Philopator)
        will arise who will send an oppressor through the Jewel of his kingdom; yet
        within a few days he will be shattered, though not in anger nor in battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And in his place [in Syria] will arise a despicable and despised
        person, to whom royal majesty and the honor of kingship have not been conferred,
        but he will come [without warning] in a time of tranquility and seize the
        kingdom by intrigue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The overwhelming forces [of the invading armies of Egypt] will be
        flooded away before him and smashed; and also the prince of the covenant
        [will be smashed]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After an alliance is made with him he will work deceitfully, and
        he will go up and gain power with a small force of people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "In a time of tranquility, [without warning] he will enter the most
        productive and richest parts of the kingdom [of Egypt], and he will accomplish
        that which his fathers never did, nor his fathers\u2019 fathers; he will
        distribute plunder, spoil and goods among them. He will devise plans against
        strongholds, but only for a time [decreed by God]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He will stir up his strength and courage against [his former Egyptian
        ally] the king of the South (Ptolemy VI) with a great army; so the king of
        the South will prepare an extremely great and powerful army to wage war,
        but he will not stand, for schemes will be devised against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Yes, those who eat his fine food will betray and destroy him (Ptolemy
        VI), and his army will be swept away, and many will fall down slain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And as for both of these kings, their hearts will be set on doing
        evil; they will speak lies over the same table, but it will not succeed,
        for the end is yet to come at the appointed time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then he (Antiochus IV Epiphanes) will return to his land with great
        treasure (plunder); and his heart will be set against the holy covenant,
        and he will take action and return to his own land (Syria).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CAt the time appointed [by God] he will return and come into
        the South, but this last time will not be successful as were the previous
        invasions [of Egypt]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'For ships of Cyprus [in Roman hands] will come against him; therefore
        he will be discouraged and turn back [to Israel] and carry out his rage against
        the holy covenant and take action; so he will return and show favoritism
        toward those [Jews] who abandon (break) the holy covenant [with God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Armed forces of his will arise [in Jerusalem] and defile and desecrate
        the sanctuary, the [spiritual] stronghold, and will do away with the regular
        sacrifice [that is, the daily burnt offering]; and they will set up [a pagan
        altar in the sanctuary which is] the abomination of desolation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'With smooth words [of flattery and praise] he will turn to godlessness
        those who [are willing to] disregard the [Mosaic] covenant, but the people
        who [are spiritually mature and] know their God will display strength and
        take action [to resist]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'They who are wise and have spiritual insight among the people will
        instruct many and help them understand; yet for many days some [of them and
        their followers] will fall by the sword and by flame, by captivity and by
        plunder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now when they fall they will receive a little help, and many will
        join with them in hypocrisy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Some of those who are [spiritually] wise and have insight will fall
        [as martyrs] in order to refine, to purge and to make those among God\u2019s
        people pure, until the end time; because it is yet to come at the time appointed
        [by God].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CThen the king (the Antichrist) will do exactly as he pleases;
        he will exalt himself and magnify himself above every god and will speak
        astounding and disgusting things against the God of gods and he will prosper
        until the indignation is finished, for that which is determined [by God]
        will be done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'He will have no regard for the gods of his fathers or for the desire
        of women, nor will he have regard for any other god, for he shall magnify
        himself above them all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Instead, he will honor a god of fortresses, a god whom his fathers
        did not know; he will honor him with gold and silver, with precious stones
        and with expensive things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'He will act against the strongest fortresses with the help of a foreign
        god; he will give great honor to those who acknowledge him and he will cause
        them to rule over the many, and will parcel out land for a price.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CAt the end time the king of the South will push and attack
        him (the Antichrist), and the king of the North will storm against him with
        chariots and horsemen and with many ships; and he will enter countries, overwhelm
        them and pass through. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'He shall also enter the Beautiful and Glorious Land (Israel), and
        many countries will fall, but these will be rescued out of his hand: Edom,
        Moab, and the foremost [core] of the people of Ammon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Then he will stretch out his hand against other countries, but Egypt
        will not be among the ones which escape. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'He will have power over the treasures of gold and silver and over
        all the precious things of Egypt, and the Libyans and the Ethiopians will
        follow in his footsteps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'But rumors from the east and from the north will alarm and disturb
        him, and he will set out with great fury to destroy and to annihilate many. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: He will pitch his palatial tents between the seas and the glorious
        Holy Mountain (Zion); yet he will come to his end with no one to help him
        [in his final battle with God].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Time of the End'
      title: The Time of the End
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CNow at that [end] time Michael, the great [angelic] prince
        who stands guard over the children of your people, will arise. And there
        will be a time of distress such as never occurred since there was a nation
        until that time; but at that time your people, everyone who is found written
        in the Book [of Life], will be rescued. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Many of those who sleep in the dust of the ground will awake (resurrect),
        these to everlasting life, but some to disgrace and everlasting contempt
        (abhorrence). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Those who are [spiritually] wise will shine brightly like the brightness
        of the expanse of heaven, and those who lead many to righteousness, [will
        shine] like the stars forever and ever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But as for you, Daniel, conceal these words and seal up the scroll
        until the end of time. Many will go back and forth and search anxiously [through
        the scroll], and knowledge [of the purpose of God as revealed by His prophets]
        will [greatly] increase.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then I, Daniel, looked, and behold, there stood two others, the one
        [angel] on this bank of the river and the other [angel] on that bank of the
        river. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And one said to the man dressed in linen, who was above the waters
        of the river, \u201CHow long will it be until the end of these wonders?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I heard the man dressed in linen, who was above the waters of
        the river, as he held up his right hand and his left hand toward heaven,
        and swore by Him who lives forever that it would be for a time, times, and
        a half a time (three and a half years); and as soon as they finish shattering
        and crushing the power of the holy people, all these things will be finished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "As for me, I heard, but I did not understand; so I said, \u201CMy
        lord, what will be the outcome of these things?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the angel said, \u201CGo your way, Daniel, for the words are
        concealed and sealed up until the end of time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Many will be purged, purified (made white) and refined, but the wicked
        will behave wickedly. None of the wicked shall understand, but those who
        are [spiritually] wise will understand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'From the time that the regular sacrifice [that is, the daily burnt
        offering] is taken away and the abomination of desolation is set up [ruining
        the temple for worship of the true God], there will be  1,290 days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'How blessed [happy, fortunate, spiritually prosperous] and beloved
        is he who waits expectantly [enduring without wavering for the period of
        tribulation] and comes to the 1,335 days! '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But as for you (Daniel), go your way until the end [of your life];
        for you will rest and rise again for your allotted inheritance at the end
        of the age.\u201D"
      comments: []
